# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# geometric-learning.form — symmetry as data: one gather operator
# carries convolution, message passing, diffusion, and embedding
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The teaching arrived via the field 2026-06-10 (Geometric Deep
# Learning, shared by @probnstat — x.com/probnstat/status/
# 2064807526005461480): learning extends beyond Euclidean grids to
# graphs, manifolds, and meshes by respecting symmetry — invariance
# and equivariance are the inductive biases, convolution generalizes
# to geometric operators, and CNNs are the special case the lattice
# gets for free. The post's diagram is f: Graph → ℝⁿ — a graph
# embedded into a manifold.
#
# The Form answer is the core-abstraction move: the domain enters as
# DATA — a list of (i j w) edge triples — and ONE engine walks every
# domain. No grid path, no graph path, no mesh path. SHIPPED:
# `form/form-stdlib/geometric-learning.fk` +
# `tests/geometric-learning-band.fk` → 4095, three-way (Go/Rust/TS).
#
#     gl-step:   y_i = Σ_{(i j w)} w · x_j      — the geometric operator
#     gl-diffuse: gl-step iterated               — heat flow on the domain
#     gl-mean:    global pooling                 — the invariant readout
#     gl-embed:   diffuse a seed, deflate mean   — f: Graph → ℝ, the
#                                                  diffusion-map coordinate
#
# Four readings of the same operator, decided by edge data alone:
#
#   Euclidean convolution   gl-ring-edges: circulant weights — the
#                           weight depends only on the offset, which IS
#                           translation symmetry visible as data symmetry
#   graph message passing   gl-mesh-edges: symmetric uniform kernel +
#                           lazy self-loops over an undirected pair list
#   diffusion               a row-stochastic kernel makes gl-step a
#                           heat step; mass conserved, the constant
#                           mode is the invariant the flow settles into
#   manifold embedding      power iteration by diffusion + constant-mode
#                           deflation — the dominant surviving mode is
#                           the domain's community/chart coordinate

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What the band proves (each a falsifiable claim, not an assertion)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Two strange-minimal domains carry all twelve claims:
#   · the 4-ring — the periodic 1-D Euclidean grid; kernel [.25 .5 .25]
#     and x = [8 4 0 4] keep every value exact in binary floats
#   · the triangular prism K3×K2 — a 3-regular mesh with two charts
#     (two triangles bridged by rungs); its second diffusion mode IS
#     the chart split (eigenvalue 2/3 vs 1/2), so power iteration
#     separates the charts provably fast
#
#   1     conv([8 4 0 4]) = [6 4 2 4]            — the CNN form lands
#   2     gl-step(circulant) ≡ gl-conv           — CNNs ARE geometric
#                                                  operators on lattices
#   4     conv(shift x) = shift(conv x)          — translation equivariance
#   8     gl-step(π·edges, π·x) = π·gl-step(edges, x)
#                                                — permutation equivariance;
#                                                  π = swap(0,1) is NOT an
#                                                  automorphism: the theorem
#                                                  is about transporting
#                                                  structure with signal
#   16    mean(π·y) = mean(y)                    — invariant readout
#   32    sum(diffuse(x,3)) = 16 exactly         — mass conservation
#   64    diffuse(x,3) = [4.5 4 3.5 4] exactly   — smoothing
#   128   diffuse(x,24) = [4 4 4 4] at 1e-6      — convergence to the
#                                                  invariant (constant mode)
#   256   embed signs (+ + + − − −)              — the two charts separate
#   512   embed[0] = 7805 at 1e-6                — pinned to the IEEE fp64
#   1024  embed[4] = −7154 at 1e-6                 oracle, fold-order exact
#   2048  embed[1]=embed[2], embed[4]=embed[5]   — the embedding recovers
#                                                  the mesh's mirror symmetry
#                                                  through the seed
#
# The conformance discipline is form-native-models': compute in fp64,
# reduce to integers at 1e-6, pin to a reference that mirrors the
# recipe's exact fold order. Determinism is the feature — every kernel
# computes the same bits.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Kinship
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   form-native-models.form     the sequence/Euclidean lane (transformer
#                               numerics, M1–M6). Attention is gl-step on
#                               the COMPLETE graph with data-dependent
#                               edge weights — softmax(QKᵀ) builds the
#                               (i j w) list each forward pass. The
#                               transformer is a GDL instance; the two
#                               lanes are one teaching.
#   ml-diffusion-model-flow.form  denoising diffusion — the generative
#                               reverse flow in latent space. This module
#                               is diffusion ON a domain (heat flow), the
#                               operator GDL generalizes convolution from.
#                               Two readings of "diffusion learning,"
#                               both now native.
#   attention.fk                the QKV walk this module's operator view
#                               re-grounds structurally.
#   mesh-relay.fk / mesh-gradient.fk  the body's own mesh tissue — the
#                               next occurrence of a hot neighborhood-
#                               aggregate wants gl-step, not a sibling.
#
# Next stones when an ask needs them (named, not built ahead of need):
# learned edge weights as recipe data (the GNN layer proper — weights
# arrive like M2's quantized tensors); data-dependent edges (attention
# as a gl-step edge builder); irregular-degree walks (1/dᵢ weights —
# the prism's 3-regularity let uniform and walk kernels coincide).
